<h4 id="bonus-what-about-ip-phones" class="headerLink">
    <a href="#bonus-what-about-ip-phones" class="header-mark" aria-label="Header mark for '(Bonus) What about IP Phones?'"></a>(Bonus) What about IP Phones?</h4><p>You may have noticed I included a vlan for phones, as this was a huge question I had on my first roll out of 802.1x. Will I need to add each phone to our Radius server and configure each phone for the authentication or use MAB<sup id="fnref:1"><a href="#fn:1" class="footnote-ref" role="doc-noteref">1</a></sup>?</p>
<p>No! Instead we will make the vlan a voice vlan with the following command which will allow the phone to use LLDP to fetch its assigned vlan bypassing its need for the authentication.</p>
